quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  19,26,"Then eat and drink and cool (your) eye, and if you see any man then say: I have vowed a fast to the Beneficent, therefore I will not speak to any man today"
  19,27,"Then she came to her people carrying him (Isa). They (her people) said, \"O Maryam !you have come with a strange thing"
  19,28,O sister of Harun ! your father was not a bad man nor your mother was one who exceeded the limits
  19,29,"So she pointed towards him (Isa, for the explanation). They said, \"How can we talk to one who is a child in the cradle?‚Äù"
  19,30,"He (Isa) said, \"I am a servant of Allah, He has given me the book and made me a prophet"
  19,31,And He has made me blessed wherever I may be and has enjoined on me worship (salat) and (giving of) charity (zakat) as long as I live
  19,32,"And (He has made me) dutiful to my mother and has not made me compelling (rebellious), wretched"
  19,33,And peace be on me the day I was born and the day I die and the day I will be raised alive
  19,34,"Such (was) Isa, the son of Maryam. (This is a) statement of the fact about which they doubt"
  19,35,"It is not befitting to Allah that He should take to Himself a son, glory be to Him, when He decrees an affair, He says to it only \"Be,\" so it is"
  19,36,"And Allah is certainly my Fosterer and your Fosterer so serve Him, this is the straight path"
  19,37,But the parties disagreed among themselves. So sorrowful will be the state of those who do not believe because of their being present on the great day
  19,38,"How clearly will they hear and how clearly will they see on the day they come to Us, but this day the unjust are in clear error"